1
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:02,980
Come in.

2
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:04,590
Morning.

3
00:00:04,590 --> 00:00:05,980
Good morning, Yakuin.

4
00:00:06,820 --> 00:00:09,240
The curling iron's still hot, so be careful, okay?

5
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:10,230
Okay.

6
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:11,980
Did she call me by my last name?

7
00:00:11,980 --> 00:00:13,800
Feels like it's been ages since she did that.

8
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:16,490
Sorry, Yakuin.

9
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:20,020
We ran out of coffee, so it's hot milk today.

10
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,120
Okay.

11
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:24,370
She really is calling me by my last name.

12
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:27,710
It doesn't seem like she's angry with me or anything, but...

13
00:00:29,350 --> 00:00:33,130
Oh, yeah. They're gonna start posting the midterm updates today, right?

14
00:00:33,130 --> 00:00:36,050
Yeah. They're gonna come through the app, right?

15
00:00:36,050 --> 00:00:39,990
We studied hard for the special tests, so we should be in a good place.

16
00:00:40,860 --> 00:00:41,980
Thanks.

17
00:00:43,140 --> 00:00:43,910
Oh, jeez.

18
00:00:44,330 --> 00:00:46,890
You've got some bedhead here, Yakuin.

19
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:49,600
I'll fix it for you later, okay?

20
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,150
S-Sure.

21
00:00:51,150 --> 00:00:52,540
Oh, that's right!

22
00:00:53,170 --> 00:00:55,550
Aside from using my last name, she's acting normal...

23
00:00:55,550 --> 00:00:57,280
or, actually, in a really good mood?

24
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:02,250
Look! Sachi gave me these chocolates yesterday!

25
00:01:02,250 --> 00:01:04,410
She said it's the super fancy stuff!

26
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:06,540
Let's eat them together tonight!

27
00:01:07,430 --> 00:01:08,300
Sure.

28
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:09,890
I can't wait!

29
00:01:09,890 --> 00:01:11,300
What is this?

30
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:13,380
What's going on?

31
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:20,710
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

32
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:31,820
It's criminal to be so shy

33
00:01:31,820 --> 00:01:35,680
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

34
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,990
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

35
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,270
No less than supreme

36
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:44,680
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

37
00:01:45,570 --> 00:01:47,290
The wild ringing of bells

38
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:54,400
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

39
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:58,080
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

40
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:03,630
A daydream that seems like fiction

41
00:02:03,630 --> 00:02:06,670
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

42
00:02:06,670 --> 00:02:09,090
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

43
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,710
My heart hurts and hurts,

44
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:16,600
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

45
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:20,080
It's TRUE FOOL LOVE! Hold me tight!

46
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,400
Be brave, my darling

47
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,980
It won't all be happy and fun

48
00:02:24,980 --> 00:02:27,000
It's all up to us

49
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,210
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

50
00:02:29,210 --> 00:02:32,860
Please look my way, darling

51
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:41,960
Please notice my pure love for you

52
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,520
girlfriend suddenly calling you by last name

53
00:02:47,770 --> 00:02:48,520
What?

54
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,510
Why are you searching for that?

55
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:52,390
Did you find yourself a girlfriend?

56
00:02:52,390 --> 00:02:54,540
Yeah, right.

57
00:02:54,540 --> 00:02:56,530
It's about Watanabe.

58
00:02:56,530 --> 00:02:57,540
What?

59
00:02:57,540 --> 00:03:01,000
You're trying to use real-life crowdsourced knowledge on Akari-chan?

60
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,060
You of all people?

61
00:03:03,060 --> 00:03:05,410
Whose side are you on?

62
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:09,220
Actually, do you and your wife argue?

63
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:10,510
We sure do!

64
00:03:10,510 --> 00:03:13,660
Not long ago, she was irritated all day.

65
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:15,440
So I asked, "Is it your period?" and patted her tummy,

66
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:18,170
and she wouldn't even talk to me for a while after that.

67
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:21,760
You are a shining example of how to get a woman to hate a man.

68
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,680
That's right. Bow down to me.

69
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:27,320
Actually, I wish my wife would just tell me things.

70
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,680
If she said she wanted me to leave her alone, I would.

71
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:34,310
Will do Read I'm buying shampoo on the way home. Which do you want?

72
00:03:29,990 --> 00:03:32,260
It'd help a lot if they'd just say something.

73
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,630
Exactly. You can pick

74
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:39,070
I'm sorry I wasn't mindful enough to notice.

75
00:03:42,070 --> 00:03:45,150
But I just can't see you that way.

76
00:03:45,150 --> 00:03:46,700
That's all right!

77
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,700
I'm in love with you, Mei-senpai!

78
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:51,210
Looks like the rumors were true.

79
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:52,960
What do you mean?

80
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:56,920
Apparently, Hamano Mei is super popular with the girls.

81
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:59,460
There was a time when everyone was talking about it.

82
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:00,910
Huh...

83
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:04,470
Wait, what does sneaking around like this say about us?

84
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,840
Thank you for falling in love with me.

85
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:11,290
Your feelings make me super happy.

86
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:16,980
Come on. You've gotta smile so you can find someone a lot better than me.

87
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:20,270
Then, just once...

88
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:21,740
Please call me by my name!

89
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,340
All right.

90
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:25,740
Once I let you go, you can't cry anymore, okay,

91
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:27,130
Manami?

92
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:28,380
Okay.

93
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:34,210
I don't know why, but I feel a tremendous sense of utter defeat.

94
00:04:34,210 --> 00:04:35,380
Same.

95
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:43,060
"I'm sorry I wasn't mindful enough to notice," huh?

96
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:47,010
It's no use!

97
00:04:47,010 --> 00:04:49,480
I thought it over all day, and I still don't get it!

98
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:53,020
What is it that I'm supposed to notice?

99
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:56,520
Why is she calling me by my last name?

100
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,220
Please call me by my name!

101
00:04:59,630 --> 00:05:01,400
...if you happened to be by my side,

102
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,340
and called me by my name...

103
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:06,820
Nah, that can't be it.

104
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:11,130
It can't be... Right?

105
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,700
I'm back!

106
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,540
She's back.

107
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:19,920
Should I try calling her by name just to check?

108
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:22,710
But if I'm wrong, it'll be embarrassing as hell!

109
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:23,280
Hey! Yes?!

110
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:26,090
Did you see the midterm updates?

111
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,840
N-No, but... right now, that's not really... Look at our ranking!

112
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,350
7th Kasugahara Kyo Sangamori Hatsune 8th Yakuin Jiro Watanabe Akari 9th Sanada Nobuyuki Honda Matsuko E-Eighth?!

113
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:32,470
That's right!

114
00:05:32,470 --> 00:05:33,090
For real? For real!

115
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,900
For really real?

116
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,400
For really real!

117
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,790
We did it!

118
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:41,520
Oh my God, we did it! I'm so happy!

119
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,040
Yay!

120
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:46,260
B-B-But first, can I take my shower?

121
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:46,960
Oh.

122
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:52,050
This shampoo was definitely the right choice!

123
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:53,680
It smells so nice!

124
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:56,540
And it says it'll make your hair super silky.

125
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:59,670
Wouldn't that be hilarious? A super silky Yakuin.

126
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:03,170
She seriously isn't calling me by my first name anymore.

127
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:06,090
I really like my name, you know?

128
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:09,090
I'm gonna start the hair dryer now.

129
00:06:10,290 --> 00:06:11,170
Akari.

130
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,600
Yakuin, it's not too hot, is it?

131
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:15,100
Akari.

132
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,830
Hey, Yakuin?

133
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,500
Akari.

134
00:06:19,590 --> 00:06:20,480
Akari.

135
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:23,400
Huh? Wait...

136
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,860
I wasn't... That was...

137
00:06:25,650 --> 00:06:27,780
What is it, Jiro?

138
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:33,490
Huh? Wait, did I actually... hit the nail on the head?

139
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,490
A-Akari.

140
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,120
What is it, Jiro?

141
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:42,640
So she really did want me to call her by her name?

142
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:43,480
Wait...

143
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,370
What?

144
00:06:45,370 --> 00:06:46,310
Akari. Jeez...

145
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:49,350
If you don't need anything, don't say my name like that.

146
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:52,650
Crap. I'm gonna start grinning.

147
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:54,510
Akari.

148
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:58,270
Stop. Don't look at my face right now.

149
00:06:58,270 --> 00:07:01,270
Th-There's no need to be that embarrassed.

150
00:07:01,270 --> 00:07:02,450
I'm not embarrassed!

151
00:07:02,450 --> 00:07:05,440
That's hot! Okay, you're not embarrassed! Of course you're not embarrassed!

152
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,350
Hot! Hot, hot, hot!

153
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:09,760
I mean, we are technically a married couple, so...

154
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:10,650
Huh?

155
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,530
I'd prefer if you'd keep calling me "Akari."

156
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,790
That's how...

157
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,540
I like it.

158
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,540
We only have a little longer to go,

159
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:25,880
so please just indulge me, Jiro.

160
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,340
That's right.

161
00:07:28,070 --> 00:07:30,800
Things will eventually go back to the way they were.

162
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:33,570
She'll go back to being Watanabe, my classmate.

163
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:47,070
Kasugahara Kyo Sangamori Hatsune Yakuin Jiro Watanabe Akari Sanada Nobuyuki Honda Matsuko For real?

164
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:48,640
That way! This is bad, Shiori!

165
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,570
Defense! Defense!

166
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:53,900
If you don't commit to doing something, you're gonna lose Yakuin!

167
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,720
Th-This again?

168
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:58,450
You didn't make any progress when you had class duty together.

169
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,960
At this rate, it'll all be over before he even notices anything.

170
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:06,220
People like Yakuin tend to go where they're pushed.

171
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:09,590
If you want to date him, you have to do more than his wife is doing!

172
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:12,540
Th-That's easy to say...

173
00:08:12,540 --> 00:08:15,510
It's possible that they've at least kissed already.

174
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:19,140
If you let your guard down, they might end up doing even more than that.

175
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:21,600
M-More than that?

176
00:08:21,850 --> 00:08:25,080
For now, I'll get things set up for you.

177
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,550
Oh, crap!

178
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:27,560
Heads up!

179
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,900
Hey! Shiori!

180
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:34,760
Is she okay?!

181
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:35,990
Oh, shit...

182
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:38,240
Shiori collapsed?

183
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:41,120
She's resting in the nurse's office. You should go see her.

184
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,640
Huh? Me?

185
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,290
You got something else to do?

186
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:49,520
No, but... I mean... I don't really have a reason to go see her.

187
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,630
Do you need a reason to check on someone who's unwell?

188
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,860
Are you embarrassed to say you're worried about her?

189
00:08:55,940 --> 00:08:58,100
If you don't want to go, that's a different story.

190
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:02,320
But if you're just trying to protect some weird sense of pride, just go.

191
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,480
Here. Take this with you.

192
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:08,480
I just don't get it, Shiori.

193
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:11,360
What do you like about a coward like him?

194
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:19,490
Oh, yeah! I sent Yakuin to you. Read Mei-chan! This is too sudden!

195
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,430
You can do this, me!

196
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,310
Excuse me.

197
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:37,750
Huh? Where's the nurse?

198
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,000
Jiro-kun?

199
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,020
Shiori?

200
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,280
You came to see me?

201
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,650
Come on in.

202
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:50,400
O-Okay.

203
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:53,830
Are you feeling better now?

204
00:09:53,830 --> 00:09:57,900
Yeah, thanks. Sorry for making you worry.

205
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:00,570
But I'm happy you came to see me.

206
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:05,520
Um, Hamano sent these. I'll leave them here.

207
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,520
Huh? You already have some.

208
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,670
Oh, Minami-kun brought those.

209
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:15,170
Oh, right. Yeah, that makes sense.

210
00:10:15,530 --> 00:10:17,060
You're married, after all.

211
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,150
It seems like things are going well.

212
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:20,800
Huh?

213
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:24,480
With you and Watanabe-san. You made it to eighth place, right?

214
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:27,850
Oh... Nah, it's more like things are finally working out.

215
00:10:27,850 --> 00:10:30,150
We're always arguing, so we lose points a lot.

216
00:10:30,150 --> 00:10:31,300
That sounds nice.

217
00:10:31,940 --> 00:10:34,740
I kinda want to try arguing with you, too.

218
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:36,070
Why?!

219
00:10:36,530 --> 00:10:38,980
Well, I've known you for such a long time,

220
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:42,230
but I've never seen you angry before.

221
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:46,900
If I became your wife, would I be able to see that, too?

222
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:51,160
Oh, I'm just talking about the practical!

223
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,430
R-Right.

224
00:10:53,170 --> 00:10:55,050
I've been feeling anxious.

225
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:59,410
I'm in high school now, but I still get nervous around boys.

226
00:10:59,410 --> 00:11:00,740
I'm a pain to deal with, huh?

227
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:02,090
Not at all!

228
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:06,370
But all the girls around me keep getting more and more mature,

229
00:11:06,370 --> 00:11:08,730
and I'm still a child.

230
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:12,970
So things with Tenjin haven't gotten... more mature?

231
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:15,980
Like, you know... kissing or whatever?

232
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:18,170
We don't do that kind of thing!

233
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:22,230
And even if things went that way with the person I loved,

234
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:24,680
I'd be terrible at it, and they'd get sick of me.

235
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:26,240
That wouldn't happen!

236
00:11:26,570 --> 00:11:28,650
Someone's first time is always precious.

237
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:31,620
If it was me, I'd be happy no matter what form it took!

238
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:36,990
H-Hey... You said before that

239
00:11:36,990 --> 00:11:41,130
if there was anything you could do to help, you would, right?

240
00:11:41,130 --> 00:11:42,570
Y-Yeah.

241
00:11:42,570 --> 00:11:44,990
Will you do me the favor I'm about to ask?

242
00:11:44,990 --> 00:11:45,890
Huh?

243
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:48,890
I want you to practice with me.

244
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:51,020
K...

245
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:52,740
Kissing.

246
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,840
I-If you don't want to, that's totally okay!

247
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,720
Sorry for just springing that on you!

248
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:04,640
It's an imposition, right? I mean, you have Watanabe-san now...

249
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,450
Why? Huh?

250
00:12:06,730 --> 00:12:08,400
Why me?

251
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:13,170
You're the only one I could ask to do this. I'm sorry.

252
00:12:13,170 --> 00:12:14,540
I don't mind at all.

253
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,800
We can practice, but, um...

254
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:19,170
I'm probably not very good at it.

255
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:22,550
Y-You're seriously okay with it being me?

256
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:30,350
If you would, I'd appreciate it.

257
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:33,260
Th-Then...

258
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:39,300
Oh, gosh, my heart is racing so fast!

259
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,090
So is mine.

260
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:44,770
That makes me happy. Our hearts are racing together.

261
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,960
I don't think it's possible...

262
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:51,660
but if Shiori... is actually serious about me...

263
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:54,390
But if you're just trying to protect some weird sense of pride, just go.

264
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:57,960
That's right! I have to go for it!

265
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,230
If I don't go for it now...

266
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,970
Wait, Jiro-kun!

267
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,060
Let's not do this after all!

268
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:14,730
We're not married. It probably wouldn't be right.

269
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:18,760
Excuse me.

270
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,870
Let me take a nap here, Sensei.

271
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:22,300
Wait, no one's here.

272
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,870
Ugh! You're at school, you know!

273
00:13:29,220 --> 00:13:31,420
Sorry for bothering you!

274
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,710
S-Sorry!

275
00:13:48,710 --> 00:13:50,640
That was an accident!

276
00:13:52,110 --> 00:13:55,070
Y-Yeah, I know. It's okay.

277
00:13:55,640 --> 00:14:00,400
So, um, Jiro-kun, I'll be okay on my own now, so...

278
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,150
R-R-Really? Th-Then I'll get going.

279
00:14:19,170 --> 00:14:22,170
Can I hang out with Sachi and the others after school? Will you be able to find something to eat? Jirooooo!

280
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:24,000
Can I hang out with Sachi and the others after school? Will you be able to find something to eat? Jirooooo!

281
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:29,050
Please answer me!

282
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,700
Don't ignore me, you idiot.

283
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:29,050
Akari! So this is where you've been.

284
00:14:29,050 --> 00:14:32,050
Sachi? Weren't you going to the nurse's office to skip class?

285
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:35,060
I tried, but it wasn't gonna happen.

286
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:37,410
When I went in, other people were there already.

287
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:40,490
Between the curtains, I could see the shoes of a guy and a girl.

288
00:14:40,490 --> 00:14:42,330
And the bed was creaking.

289
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:45,190
Huh? What do you mean? You think they were doing that?

290
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:49,210
What else could a guy and a girl be doing to make a bed creak?

291
00:14:49,210 --> 00:14:51,500
Seriously, what the hell are they thinking?

292
00:14:53,330 --> 00:14:55,830
Sorry. Shiori collapsed, so I was in the nurse's office. Got it. Jirooooo! Please answer me!

293
00:14:55,830 --> 00:14:59,710
Sorry. Shiori collapsed, so I was in the nurse's office. Got it.

294
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,770
No way.

295
00:14:57,770 --> 00:14:59,710
Akari? What is it?

296
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:02,360
Jiro...

297
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:11,090
Let's eat it together!

298
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:17,100
7/5 Wednesday Akari's pretty late.

299
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:25,610
Sorry we couldn't do an all-nighter You seem down. What's wrong? If it's something you can talk about, tell us Natsumi's worried about you, too

300
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,730
Oh, Mikkun, you were about to clock out, weren't you?

301
00:15:31,070 --> 00:15:32,740
Sorry. I just need whipped cream on this.

302
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:34,740
Got it.

303
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:38,120
The one who ordered it is a serious gyaru,

304
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:41,990
but she seemed kinda down, so you can give her a little extra for free.

305
00:15:41,990 --> 00:15:43,040
Really?

306
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,600
Thank you for waiting!

307
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,170
Please enjoy at your leisure.

308
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:54,830
It's so good! And sweet!

309
00:15:54,830 --> 00:15:55,680
Huh?

310
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,680
Extra whipped cream on the house. Hope it cheers you up.

311
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,560
Huh? Oh, crap! Did it show on my face?

312
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:02,310
How embarrassing!

313
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:06,310
Oh, I get it. I'm...

314
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:08,450
feeling depressed.

315
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,300
That guy's actually really nice.

316
00:16:15,110 --> 00:16:19,080
Did Jiro really do that with Sakurazaka-san?

317
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:21,340
He said she's his first love, right?

318
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:27,340
Having your first time be with your first love would make anyone happy.

319
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:31,100
Just because Jiro and Sakurazaka-san are together now

320
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,990
doesn't mean anything's changed.

321
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:37,050
Jiro and I are a married couple right now, that's all.

322
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:39,130
It's nothing more than that, and yet...

323
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:42,770
If I open this door right now,

324
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:45,570
I feel like there'll be a Jiro there that I don't know.

325
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:51,360
Is he already asleep?

326
00:16:58,310 --> 00:17:00,460
Why are you sleeping there?

327
00:17:00,460 --> 00:17:03,320
And why are all your dirty clothes scattered everywhere?

328
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:06,290
I told you not to roll up your socks like that!

329
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:08,500
What am I, your mother?

330
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:12,830
Come on! I'm stepping on the pedal, but it won't...

331
00:17:12,830 --> 00:17:14,010
Argh!

332
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:18,690
Got it!

333
00:17:18,690 --> 00:17:19,730
Ugh!

334
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:22,340
I'm gonna start throwing my dirty clothes everywhere, too!

335
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:23,520
Are you okay with that?

336
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:26,500
And if you're going to sleep, sleep in your room!

337
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,520
And you could at least vacuum!

338
00:17:27,310 --> 00:17:33,150
7/5 Wednesday I just found out... Those chocolates have whiskey in them! You haven't eaten them, have you?!

339
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:30,440
Learn to cook something!

340
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:33,150
And I'm shouting here, so wake up already!

341
00:17:33,390 --> 00:17:36,700
Jeez... My depression just disappeared.

342
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:39,390
The table's all messy, too...

343
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:43,790
You were waiting for me?

344
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,440
Idiot.

345
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:54,220
Hey, Jiro? Are you listening?

346
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:11,230
You're really not gonna wake up?

347
00:18:11,230 --> 00:18:12,570
Are you alive?

348
00:18:12,990 --> 00:18:15,570
Your wife is taking off her clothes here, you know.

349
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:21,740
Hey, Jiro...

350
00:18:21,740 --> 00:18:25,450
Is this what you did in the nurse's office?

351
00:18:25,450 --> 00:18:26,580
Or was it...

352
00:18:27,450 --> 00:18:30,720
something far beyond this that I don't even know about?

353
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:34,650
Did you go off and become an adult without me?

354
00:18:35,660 --> 00:18:38,390
I'd hate that. Don't leave me behind.

355
00:18:39,940 --> 00:18:44,100
You know, I really will cheer you on in your love.

356
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:47,400
So just for now, while I'm your wife, could you wait?

357
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,600
Please, Jiro.

358
00:18:57,850 --> 00:18:59,930
Ow, my arm...

359
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:03,990
Wha?!

360
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:07,000
Why? Why is she sleeping next to me?!

361
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,540
And what happened to her clothes?!

362
00:19:12,350 --> 00:19:14,380
Good morning, Jiro.

363
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:19,090
What's wrong? I said good morning.

364
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:20,590
Hey!

365
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,720
Huh? What? What's wrong with you?

366
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,180
That's what I want to ask you!

367
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:28,180
Wh-What happened to your clothes? I can see everything!

368
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,690
You didn't even realize it?!

369
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:37,830
I have a ton of questions, but first, please put some clothes on.

370
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:38,890
We can talk after—

371
00:19:38,890 --> 00:19:40,070
What's the point now?

372
00:19:40,940 --> 00:19:43,020
You're the one who took them off of me.

373
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:49,190
Wow, you're scum! You really forgot what happened last night?

374
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:50,800
H-Hang on. Time out.

375
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,290
What?

376
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:54,330
You really don't remember! What a jerk!

377
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:57,090
Even after all you did to me...

378
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,630
Don't!

379
00:19:58,630 --> 00:20:00,720
After "all" I did?!

380
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:03,630
Wait, wait. I have absolutely no memory of anything.

381
00:20:03,630 --> 00:20:05,440
Does that mean we did it?

382
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:08,720
That we went as far as it's possible to go?

383
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,020
No, wait.

384
00:20:10,450 --> 00:20:12,570
She has Tenjin, but she'd let me have her body?

385
00:20:12,570 --> 00:20:16,020
Yeah, as if things would ever get like that between us, anyway...

386
00:20:19,410 --> 00:20:21,150
Except they already did!

387
00:20:22,210 --> 00:20:23,240
Wait!

388
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,600
I'm not a virgin anymore?

389
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,660
Huh? Wh-Why are you asking me?!

390
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:29,390
Let go of me, you idiot!

391
00:20:29,390 --> 00:20:30,790
Oh, s-sorry.

392
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:36,440
If we really did do it, I'd be absolute scum not to remember, right?

393
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,670
I mean, it probably...

394
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:41,020
wasn't just my first time.

395
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,640
Hey, Jiro...

396
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,480
Was last night your first time?

397
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,450
Last night?!

398
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:48,040
If it happened... then it was.

399
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,100
Really?

400
00:20:49,460 --> 00:20:52,060
If you're lying, you don't get any dinner.

401
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:56,060
It was. Why would I lie about that now?

402
00:20:56,420 --> 00:20:58,060
I see.

403
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:00,080
So it was.

404
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:01,370
Also... sorry.

405
00:21:01,370 --> 00:21:02,320
Huh?

406
00:21:02,570 --> 00:21:05,320
I mean, since I was a virgin...

407
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:08,720
I probably put most of the burden on you.

408
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:11,410
It must have been difficult and painful because of m—

409
00:21:11,410 --> 00:21:12,680
I was lying.

410
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:13,580
Huh?

411
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:14,960
I lied.

412
00:21:15,260 --> 00:21:16,970
Isn't that obvious?

413
00:21:16,970 --> 00:21:18,880
Of course it was all a lie!

414
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,720
Talk about hilarious!

415
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:21,590
You...

416
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:24,410
You've gotta be kidding me!

417
00:21:24,410 --> 00:21:26,090
You fell for it!

418
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:28,990
You should know I'm not that easy!

419
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:34,540
Jeez... There are some lies that are just not okay, you know!

420
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:36,920
But, yeah... Yeah, of course.

421
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:40,360
Come on. You could act a little disappointed, couldn't you?

422
00:21:40,740 --> 00:21:43,110
Well, of course I'm disappointed.

423
00:21:45,090 --> 00:21:47,490
I mean, I'm still a virgin.

424
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:50,780
Ow! That hurts! Ow! Ow! Ow!

425
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:51,600
I'm sorry!

426
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,280
Of course you'd never do that with a guy like me, right?

427
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,750
I was being presumptuous!

428
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:56,870
It's not that!

429
00:21:57,920 --> 00:22:01,750
I'd never do that when I know you have Sakurazaka-san.

430
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:04,030
Huh? What did you say?

431
00:22:04,030 --> 00:22:07,650
"I hate that my first time was with a girl I don't even love."

432
00:22:07,650 --> 00:22:09,880
"I wish it had been Sakurazaka-san instead."

433
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,300
That's how you felt, right?

434
00:22:10,510 --> 00:22:12,390
Hey, I can't hear you!

435
00:22:12,390 --> 00:22:14,020
Why don't you just say that?

436
00:22:14,020 --> 00:22:15,770
I don't know what you're saying!

437
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,120
I hate you, Jiro.

438
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:23,920
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

439
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:28,350
I want to give love a try

440
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,260
In this night when everything begins to overflow

441
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,530
I match my stride to yours

442
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:39,370
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

443
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:43,940
The answers always slip away

444
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,360
All I want is to do it over again

445
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,760
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

446
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:57,060
I want to know where my heart is hiding

447
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,840
One day this will end

448
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,640
I know that

449
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,350
And I know the signs of discord

450
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,400
Turn them inside out

451
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't let them pile up

452
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,210
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

453
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,250
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

454
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:22,680
I want to give love a try

455
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,700
Everything begins to overflow

456
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,890
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

457
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:36,150
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

458
00:23:51,710 --> 00:23:55,290
What a nice feeling. I'd like to fall asleep just like this.

459
00:23:55,290 --> 00:23:57,490
Jiro-kun, come to me.

460
00:23:57,490 --> 00:23:58,720
Shiori!

461
00:23:57,490 --> 00:23:59,780
There's one Jiro-kun.

462
00:23:59,780 --> 00:24:00,900
Shiori! And two Jiro-kuns.

463
00:24:01,790 --> 00:24:03,500
There's three Jiro-kuns. Shiori!

464
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,010
Next Time Fireworks, but No Embrace. Next time, "Fireworks, but No Embrace."

